<br>
I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> highly</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> recommend 5-6 groups for Vox.  Mainly because you need to have at least a partial group keeping the giants cleared while you buff.  This group can also engage any remaining guardians in Vox's chamber if they can't be pulled (I've heard that can be a problem sometimes).<br>
<br>
A few suggestions:  Make sure you know where the pit traps are.  I once had a MT run right into a pit on the initial charge - that didn't help.<br>
<br>
Also, mana sieve and stun are your friends.  Chanters should be sieving from basically the beginning, and everyone that has a stun should use it when she starts getting low on HP.  The stuns won't stick, but they can still interrupt casting (I've heard).  Having the melee's push all on one side I've heard helps too.<br>
<br>
Just saw you are gonna have your MT pull - bad idea.  Get a monk to pull.  Period.  If it was me, there would be no raid without a monk (or maybe SK) to pull.   You just gotta have the FD capability to stand a chance.<br>
<br>
If at all possible, have a 52 warrior be the MT so he/she can use Evasive disc on the dragon - makes a big difference.<br>
<br>
********** Guide Links ********** <br>
<br>
Here are a couple links to decent Vox raid guides. Please read through both guides - they have valuable information, maps, tips, etc.  The first link also has suggestions for reducing lag.  I highly recommend everyone take measures to reduce lag - nothing sucks worse than going LD right as everyone charges the dragon (possibly the highest lag moment of the raid).<br>
<br>
www.angelfire.com/rpg/ladyvoxdruzzilro/<br>
www.crimsontalon.com/raidvox.htm<br>
<br>
********* LOOT ********* <br>
<br>
